B.SK=new A.dG("Inconsistent spacing and visual hierarchy across screens","Card padding, heading sizes, and label styles varied across the dashboard, making it harder to scan quickly \u2014 a significant issue for practitioners working under time pressure.",B.cD,"Nielsen H4: Consistency and Standards","Standardised spacing tokens and type scale applied across all screens in the second iteration.")
B.SJ=new A.dG("Unclear copy on AI-enabled actions","Labels on AI-generated outputs did not make it obvious that the content was AI-produced, or that it required practitioner review before use.",B.cD,"Nielsen H1: Visibility of System Status","Explicit \u201cAI-generated \u2014 review before sending\u201d labels added to all AI outputs, with a distinct visual treatment separating them from practitioner-authored content.")
B.SV=new A.dG("Weak visual affordance on interactive elements","Several action buttons and session cards did not communicate their interactivity clearly, leading the usability participant to hesitate before interacting.",B.dx,"Nielsen H7: Flexibility and Efficiency / 2.4.7 Focus Visible","Hover and focus states added. Primary actions given stronger visual weight with filled button styles.")
B.SX=new A.dG("No system feedback after voice commands","The initial voice assistant prototype gave no visible feedback that a command had been received or understood, leaving practitioners uncertain whether to repeat themselves.",B.dx,"Nielsen H1: Visibility of System Status","A brief animated confirmation state added between command input and checklist generation, confirming the assistant had processed the instruction.")
B.Mx=s([B.SK,B.SJ,B.SV,B.SX],t.jW)
B.SY=new A.uO(B.a5,B.Mx,"Accessibility and usability issues found","Issues surfaced during heuristic evaluation (Nielsen\u2019s ten heuristics) and addressed before practitioner testing.",null)
B.SM=new A.dG("No progress indicator in a five-screen flow","People had no way to gauge how far through onboarding they were or how much was left, which fed straight into the sense that the effort was open-ended.",B.cD,"2.4.8 Location","Added a step indicator to every onboarding screen, showing current position and total steps.")
B.SQ=new A.dG("System permission dialogs appeared with no context","OS-level prompts for location and notifications arrived abruptly with no prior explanation. For anyone using a screen reader, the sudden modal shift was especially disorienting.",B.cD,"3.3.2 Labels or Instructions","Added a dedicated explainer screen before each OS prompt, with a plain-language reason and benefit for each permission requested.")
B.SP=new A.dG("Avatar selection wasn\u2019t usable with VoiceOver or TalkBack","The initial avatar grid used tap targets that were too small and had no accessible labels, making selection hard for anyone navigating by touch or screen reader.",B.cD,"2.5.5 Target Size / 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value","Increased avatar tap targets to a minimum of 48x48dp and gave each one a semantic label describing the breed or character.")
B.SR=new A.dG("Optional fields weren\u2019t labelled as optional","Photo upload and several profile fields were effectively optional but weren\u2019t marked as such, so people assumed they had to complete them to proceed.",B.dx,"3.3.2 Labels or Instructions","Labelled optional fields explicitly as \u201cOptional \u2014 you can add this later\u201d and added skip affordances where relevant.")
B.ST=new A.dG("The feature carousel had no pause or manual control","The carousel auto-advanced on a timer with no way to pause or step through it, which is a problem for anyone who needs more time to read.",B.dx,"2.2.2 Pause, Stop, Hide","Made the carousel manually navigated by default, with swipe and dot-tap controls, and removed the auto-advance.")
B.LS=s([B.SM,B.SQ,B.SP,B.SR,B.ST],t.jW)
B.SZ=new A.uO(B.av,B.LS,"Accessibility considerations","Issues that came up during the heuristic review, fixed as part of the redesign rather than filed for later.",null)
B.T0=new A.uP(B.O,"Before","A single scrolling page that piled marketing preferences, assumptions and declarations, cover details and payment into one view, mostly as paragraphs of text. The information was technically all there, but it expected you to read the whole thing \u2014 and gave you little reason to trust the brand before asking you to commit.","After","A two-page flow. Page one leads with price and trust signals, then cover details, warranty questions and personal information. Page two handles assumptions and declarations \u2014 including an explicit, acknowledged call-out of the pre-existing conditions rules \u2014 before payment. All the FCA-mandated language is still there; it's just no longer cluttering the page and has been laid out so it's easier to consume.",null)
B.T1=new A.uP(B.av,"Before","Five screens, sixteen questions, a mandatory photo upload, abrupt system permission prompts, and no explanation anywhere of what Perro actually offered. It asked for a lot and gave very little back before the first moment that might have made someone care.","After","Four screens and eleven questions, with the avatar system and optional photo, a feature carousel front-loading the value, a permissions explainer, and a subscription step that carries the same story through to the end. Setup stopped feeling like paperwork and started feeling like an introduction.",null)
B.oR=new A.dp(61298,"MaterialIcons",null,!1)
B.jM=new A.yb(1,"principle")
B.T3=new A.ll(B.O,"Through every layout decision there was one question I kept dragging things back to: does this make it easier for someone to understand what they're actually looking at? I cared about visual consistency and brand alignment too \u2014 but surfacing the right information at the right moment came first.","Design principle",B.oR,B.jM,null)
B.nb=new A.yb(0,"insight")
B.T5=new A.ll(B.a5,"The sample of seven practitioners provided rich qualitative insight but limits generalisability. The low-contact workshop introduced delays and occasional ambiguity. The current output is at the prototype and concept-validation stage; future work would involve building an MVP integrated with real Google or Microsoft APIs, trialling it in practice with a small cohort, and adding quantitative usability measurement alongside the qualitative methods.","Limitations and future work",B.oR,B.nb,null)
B.H0=new A.dp(983357,"MaterialIcons",null,!1)
B.T6=new A.ll(B.a5,"Design a practical, practitioner-centred tool that streamlines administrative tasks and supports mental health professionals before, during and after counselling sessions \u2014 without compromising the therapeutic relationship or introducing ethical risk.","Research aim",B.H0,B.jM,null)
B.GX=new A.dp(62329,"MaterialIcons",null,!1)
B.Dq=new A.yb(2,"warning")
B.T7=new A.ll(B.a5,"Using RRI prompts and Moral IT cards, I mapped all stakeholders and systematically interrogated data flows, consent boundaries, and AI usage risks. Key outcomes: AI limited to non-diagnostic roles only (summarisation, scheduling prompts); per-client AI toggles required; on-device or privacy-preserving architectures favoured; explicit practitioner approval required before any client-facing action.","RRI ethical review",B.GX,B.Dq,null)
B.H1=new A.dp(984664,"MaterialIcons",null,!1)
B.T8=new A.ll(B.av,"Three ideas shaped more or less every decision I made. Shorten and refocus onboarding around what actually improves the first session rather than what\u2019s nice to have on file. Lead with value before asking for anything. And go after the specific friction points the research had surfaced, namely the photo upload, the unexplained permissions and the late-funnel fatigue, rather than redesigning for the sake of it.","Strategy",B.H1,B.jM,null)
B.bd=new A.yV("Positive",0,"positive")
B.Tn=new A.d0("Pre-existing conditions got their own page with an explicit tick-box","All eleven raised it unprompted. A checkbox buried in an assumptions section was never going to fix a misunderstanding this fundamental.","Stanley from Finance summed it up: \"Having it as its own page \u2014 we're not hiding it. It's quite helpful.\" Kerry noted it changes the claims conversation, since customers have declared from the outset.",B.bd)
B.Tl=new A.d0("Excess moved to page one","It was missing entirely, which was both a clarity gap and a missed marketing opportunity given it's one of the lowest excesses in the market.","Now visible alongside cover details, presented as a feature rather than a buried disclosure.",B.bd)
B.k9=new A.yV("Trade-off",2,"tradeoff")
B.Tb=new A.d0("A qualifier was added to the lifetime cover headline","The unconditional wording sets an expectation the policy can't always keep, and pre-existing exclusions are the most common reason a claim is declined.",'Something like "subject to your pet\'s health history" keeps it accurate without changing the meaning for most customers. Flagged to copy and compliance.',B.k9)
