B.Th=new A.d0("AI features made opt-in on a per-client basis, not globally","Practitioners had strong and varied views on AI in clinical contexts. A single on/off toggle felt too blunt; per-client control let each practitioner calibrate based on their own clinical judgement and the nature of each therapeutic relationship.","Usability session participant responded positively to the granularity. The toggle became a visible signal of practitioner agency, not just a compliance checkbox.",B.bd)
B.Tr=new A.d0("Voice assistant outputs shown as editable checklists before execution","Early thinking around voice-first interfaces assumed direct execution would feel faster. Research made clear that practitioners need to see and approve what the system intends to do before it acts \u2014 especially for anything client-facing.","The checklist model removed the core fear of automated errors in clinical communication. Participants described it as the feature that made the voice assistant feel trustworthy rather than risky.",B.bd)
