B.Tp=new A.d0("Took pet illnesses and detailed health information out of onboarding entirely","These fields sat early, added real perceived effort, and offered nothing back in the first session. People weren\u2019t invested enough yet to feel it was a fair trade.","A major resistance point disappeared. The information moved to a later in-app prompt, where people had the context and the motivation to give it.",B.bd)
B.Tc=new A.d0("Led with a feature carousel before the first form screen","Both the competitive analysis and the sessions pointed at the same gap \u2014 people had no idea what Perro would do for them before being asked to hand over information.","Tested against a minimal version without it. The carousel did better on engagement and downstream completion, and became the production baseline.",B.bd)
B.Te=new A.d0("Replaced mandatory photo upload with an avatar system and optional image","Sessions showed this was a silent exit trigger. People left to find a suitable photo and frequently didn\u2019t come back, so making it optional removed a low-value blocker.","Drop-off at the dog profile step fell noticeably after launch, and people could finish setup in one sitting without leaving the app.",B.bd)
B.Tm=new A.d0("Added a plain-language permissions explainer before the OS prompts","Abrupt system dialogs for location and notifications appeared out of nowhere. Most people either dismissed them or felt ambushed.","Acceptance improved. People who read the explainer were far more likely to grant both location and notification access.",B.bd)
B.Tf=new A.d0("Echoed the carousel benefits on the subscription screen","The paywall used to feel disconnected from the onboarding story. Repeating the same four benefit areas tied it back in.","Subscription conversion rose and more people chose longer-term plans. Feedback described the step as feeling \u201cfairer\u201d and \u201cmore honest\u201d.",B.bd)
B.Tq=new A.d0("Moved activity level and some fitness questions to post-signup prompts","They were arriving when people were already fatigued, and before they\u2019d done anything in the app that made the questions feel relevant.","Late-funnel fatigue dropped. The information still gets collected, just at a point where people have a reason to care about it.",B.bd)
